ok8JRiuSmp3Oxt403-5yOK_5xJi-n-msh7bjvHdaS_L3GjeoL4FITNS3qxV8TNDiXCG_IeGb9Qv=
bdIcGnf4gTxGJsKCHj9yPkts3FKKo9GhGzj2j5LyTq_2H_gGSRJFG]. Subscribers grew 53=
% in one month.=C2=A0
Not Boring was still tiny, but it was starting to find that elusive *produc=
t-market fit*. Plus, people were stuck at home and bored. It was time to st=
art focusing on growth.=C2=A0
Lesson: Lean into the intersection of what you=E2=80=99re passionate about =
and what=E2=80=99s different about you.
Growth: Luck, Shares, Ups, Downs, and Tommy
In May 2020, one year into writing a newsletter, I wrote Looking Back, Forw=
ard, and Up [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkMluhDAMQL9mcgNlIdshh176G=
yiLYaKBBIVQxN83ZapWchzJlv3k522FOZfLbHmv6CeN9drAJDj3BWqFgo4dyhiDIYIqxgeNghkC=
UVyhuI9TAVhtXEwtB6DtcEv0tsac7gmMKUdPg5XDxIGVkxRWM6aUE0CwAC2Y1UK8ufYIEZIHA19=
QrpwALeZZ67Y_2MeDfrY4z7NPubpcYpp7n1tpa2_J-dUKnbP-1U25nLaEzqbQHRuKhmJK8IA5oZ=
ww2pOeUaaIFZozHyY1Eau9BymIZ04NgYvHgNeZ9vvh9to2Ns6KivnjtvbraVdY7ka7eGz_eqRYr=
xGSdQuEt4z6dnrrGWdIUJrrMNraTBIpqMRaUvx7fLPFBsklxho1cshtKv1DvwGnAY2r] to ref=
lect on one year of writing and set goals for the future. My first goal was=
 to hit 5,000 subscribers by the end of the summer, and then turn on paid s=
ubscriptions. From that piece:=C2=A0
Goal #1: Grow to 5,000 Subscribers by Labor Day and 10,000 by May 21, 2021
It took ten months to get to 500, but less than two to get from there to 1,=
294. I=E2=80=99ll be testing a bunch of tactics over the next few months to=
 get to 5,000, but the most important will be continuing to improve the con=
tent and provide more value so that you want to share it with your smartest=
 friends.=C2=A0
Last April, my brother Dan and I I retreated to the beach, shaved off our o=
vergrown pandemic hair, and brainstormed. We decided the best path was to c=
ome up with a list of 100 growth ideas. We got to eleven, and did maybe thr=
ee of them. I=E2=80=99m not a growth hack person.
The most important growth levers over the past year ended up being really s=
imple: quality and consistency. Show up enough for good things to happen ev=
ery once in a while.=C2=A0
From the 473 people that received the last Per My Last Email, we=E2=80=99re=
 now at 42,205 a year later -- 8,803% growth =F0=9F=93=88 . That growth did=
n=E2=80=99t happen in a straight line.=C2=A0
This is net of unsubscribes. A lot of people unsubscribed over the course o=
f the year. As a newsletter writer, you=E2=80=99re supposed to say, =E2=80=
=9CHey, I appreciate that they gave me a chance, and if it wasn=E2=80=99t f=
or them, I=E2=80=99m happy they left!=E2=80=9D That=E2=80=99s not how I thi=
nk about it. Every time I see an unsubscribe email I take it personally and=
 get pissed at the unsubscriber. That=E2=80=99s probably not going to chang=
e.
To read more about growth, luck, my writing process, the Syndicate, how it =
all fits together in the Not Boring Flywheel, and the future of Not Boring=
